						               													<description>Colonnade is a two person game which uses a 1x8 board, 12 red checkers and 12 blue checkers.  The board is initially set up as shown in the figure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can pick up any one of your checkers from a stack, carrying the checkers above it along, and place it onto an adjacent stack that&amp;rsquo;s topped with a checker of your color. (A stack can be of height 1.)  Complete such a move with a discard.  I.e. if two like-colored checkers are adjacent in a stack, discard one of the two checkers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can also move a checker down to an unoccupied square.  You can't slide a bottom checker sideways to an unoccupied square.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The last player to have a move available wins.  I.e. if you don't have a move available on your turn, you lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
